fields.name: nigiri salmon
fields.recipe:
- ​​Prepare sushi rice by cooking and seasoning it with rice vinegar, sugar, and salt. Allow it to cool to room temperature.
- Slice your desired seafood (such as salmon, tuna, or shrimp) into thin, uniform pieces. Ensure it is fresh and sushi-grade.
- Wet your hands slightly with water to prevent the rice from sticking. Take a small amount of sushi rice and shape it into oblong-shaped balls, about 2 tablespoons each.
- Optionally, place a small amount of wasabi paste on top of each rice ball.
- Take a slice of your prepared seafood and gently drape it over the rice ball, ensuring that it covers the top completely.
- If desired, wrap a strip of nori around the sides of the rice and seafood to hold them together, or press the seafood gently onto the rice to adhere.
- Repeat the process with the remaining rice and seafood slices.
- Serve the nigiri sushi with soy sauce, pickled ginger, and wasabi on the side for dipping.
- Enjoy your homemade nigiri sushi!

fields.name: philadelphia roll
fields.recipe:
- Lay a sheet of nori on a bamboo sushi mat (makisu) with the shiny side facing down.
- Moisten your hands with water to prevent the rice from sticking. Take a handful of sushi rice and spread it evenly over the nori, leaving a small border along the top edge.
- Flip the nori sheet over so that the rice side is facing down on the sushi mat.
- Spread a layer of Philadelphia cream cheese evenly over the nori sheet.
- Arrange slices of fresh fish, cucumber strips, and avocado slices along the bottom edge of the nori sheet.
- Using the bamboo mat, carefully roll the nori sheet over the filling, applying gentle pressure to shape it into a tight cylinder.
- Once rolled, use the bamboo mat to shape and tighten the roll further.
- Sprinkle sesame seeds over the top of the roll, if desired, for added texture and flavor.
- Use a sharp knife to slice the roll into individual pieces, wiping the knife with a damp cloth between cuts to ensure clean slices.

fields.name: thai salad with shrimps
fields.recipe:
- Cook the shrimp: Bring a pot of salted water to a boil. Add the shrimp and cook until pink and opaque, about 2-3 minutes. Drain and set aside to cool.
- Prepare the dressing: In a small bowl, whisk together the fish sauce, lime juice, soy sauce, brown sugar, minced garlic, grated ginger, and vegetable oil until well combined. Set aside.
- In a large mixing bowl, combine the chopped lettuce, sliced cucumber, grated carrot, thinly sliced red onion, chopped cilantro, chopped mint, sliced red chili (if using), and cooked shrimp.
- Pour the prepared dressing over the salad ingredients and toss gently to coat everything evenly.
- Sprinkle chopped roasted peanuts over the salad for added crunch and flavor.
- Serve the Thai shrimp salad immediately, garnished with extra cilantro or mint leaves if desired.
- Enjoy your delicious and refreshing Thai shrimp salad!

fields.name: thai salad with chicken
fields.recipe:
- Cook the chicken on the pan about 2-3 minutes with say sauce.Drain and set aside to cool.
- Prepare the dressing: In a small bowl, whisk together the say sauce, lime juice, soy sauce, brown sugar, minced garlic, grated ginger, and vegetable oil until well combined. Set aside.
- In a large mixing bowl, combine the chopped lettuce, sliced cucumber, grated carrot, thinly sliced red onion, chopped cilantro, chopped mint, sliced red chili (if using), and cooked chicken.

- Enjoy your delicious and refreshing Thai chicken salad!

fields.name: sashimi salmon
fields.recipe:
- Begin by selecting high-quality, sashimi-grade fish from a reputable fishmonger or market. Ensure that the fish is fresh, properly handled, and safe for raw consumption.
- Rinse the fish under cold water and pat it dry with paper towels. Use a sharp knife to slice the fish into thin, uniform slices. Slice against the grain for a tender texture.
- Arrange the sliced fish on a serving platter in an attractive manner. You can create a decorative pattern or simply lay the slices flat.
- Serve the sashimi with small dollops of wasabi paste on the side. Wasabi adds heat and flavor to the sashimi, but it should be used sparingly as it can be quite potent.
- Provide soy sauce in small dipping bowls for guests to dip their sashimi slices. Soy sauce adds saltiness and enhances the flavor of the fish.
- Optionally, serve pickled ginger on the side. Pickled ginger is traditionally eaten between bites of sashimi to cleanse the palate.
- Garnish the sashimi platter with shiso leaves for a decorative touch and added flavor, if desired.
- Enjoy your delicious homemade sashimi as a refreshing and elegant appetizer or main course.

fields.name: Tom Yum Soup
fields.recipe:
- In a pot, bring the chicken or vegetable broth to a boil.
- Add the lemongrass, galangal or ginger slices, kaffir lime leaves, and sliced red chili peppers to the boiling broth. Simmer for 5-10 minutes to infuse the flavors.
- Add the shrimp and mushrooms to the pot and cook until the shrimp turn pink and opaque, and the mushrooms are tender, about 3-5 minutes.
- Stir in the fish sauce and lime juice. Taste the soup and adjust the seasoning with salt if needed.
- Remove the pot from heat and ladle the hot soup into serving bowls.
- Garnish with chopped cilantro, if desired, and serve immediately.
